# Vue SFC — BEM and scoped SCSS

**CSS class naming** + **`<style lang="scss">`** only. Not `data-test-*` hooks ([vue-template-test-hooks.mdc](vue-template-test-hooks.mdc)) or `<script setup>` ([vue-quasar.mdc](vue-quasar.mdc)).

## Block and element classes (template)

Follow [GlobalWindowButtons.vue](src/components/globals/GlobalWindowButtons/GlobalWindowButtons.vue), [AppControlMenus.vue](src/components/globals/AppControlMenus/AppControlMenus.vue):

- **Block**: one root class, lowerCamelCase (e.g. `globalWindowButtons`, `appControlMenus`).
- **Elements**: `blockName__element` (double underscore), e.g. `globalWindowButtons__button`, `appControlMenus__inner`.
- **Quasar / utilities**: keep existing Quasar props + utility classes (`flat`, `bg-dark`, etc.) on same nodes when codebase combines with BEM.

Use **HTML comments** in template to group sections (buttons, tooltips, regions) like existing components.

## Scoped SCSS

- Prefer `<style lang="scss" scoped>` unless unscoped intentional (match neighbors).
- Do **not** introduce new raw **colors** or **sized units** (`px`, `rem`, `vh`, etc.) in component SCSS when they belong in shared token set. Add/reuse variables in feature **`styles/_variables.scss`**, [src/css/theme/quasar-components/](src/css/theme/quasar-components/) (for `q-*` global overrides), or [app.palette.scss](src/css/app.palette.scss). Theme **`$` identifiers**: **hyphens** between segments (never underscores in `$` identifiers). Applies to `<style>` only, not template attributes/prop strings unless policy expands.
- Do **not** use **framework palette** Sass variables (`$primary`, `$grey`, `$white`, `$dark`, `$accent`, …) directly in component SCSS. Add **semantic** token in catalogue — same indirection as raw sizes/hex ([project-scss.mdc](project-scss.mdc) **Palette variables vs semantic color tokens**). Reuse semantic Globals (e.g. `$aLinkColor`) when role matches.
- Nest element rules under block:

```scss
.appControlMenus {
  &__inner {
    -webkit-app-region: no-drag;
  }
}
```

- Avoid deep nesting; prefer extra element classes over long compound selectors.

## Global / shared styles

Cross-app SCSS under [src/css](src/css) — [project-scss.mdc](project-scss.mdc). Component BEM in SFC **or**, when external sheet required (usually SFC size), feature **`styles/`** — [component-styles-folder.mdc](component-styles-folder.mdc).
